id=acc
domain=vr25
name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-dev-fix9
versionCode=202505183
author=VR25 (community fix9)
description=[community fix9: full fail-safe coverage on all capacity limits, flat-hold on all charge-limit nodes, and a breach watchdog that warns if the cap is not holding. fix8: malformed-config fail-safe + locked-switch recovery. fix7: Pixel/Tensor cap now HOLDS at the limit. Drives the google charge_stop_level node to pause_capacity so the firmware holds the battery flat at the cap (tight, no overshoot, true idle) instead of toggling 100/5 and sawtoothing past it; switch scanner prefers idle/flat-hold switches; restores retry-on-stall (no daemon re-init mid-pause). Includes fix2-fix6.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
